## Important

- Every component reference must use actual Harmony component names from the component list (read from harmony skill or `src/components/ui/index.ts`).
- Every prop in the Implementation section must come from the actual Harmony component docs, not invented.
- If a pattern needs a component that doesn't exist in Harmony, note it in the pattern doc as "Not in Harmony — implement as custom component using Harmony tokens."
- The Component Tree section is required for every pattern — the layout-builder skill reads it for composition.
- Do not generate the Accordion Wizard pattern if "Wizard Dialog" already exists in the registry.
- For patterns sourced from the Harmony Functionality PDF, reference the relevant page/section in the pattern doc's Design Decisions section so designers can trace back to the original spec.
- Card Grid variations (1-col, 2-col, 2x2, 3+1, 4-col) should be documented as variants within the single Card Grid pattern, not as separate patterns.

## Optional flags

- `--category [name]`: Generate only patterns in that category (e.g. `--category forms`).
- `--dry-run`: List the patterns that would be generated without creating files.
- `--product [name]`: Override product (default: cross-product).